snippet.textDisplay:
OU fan / college football fan. Love this channel. Such an accurate depiction.

LSU is king this year. Bama had down year but probably feeling lower than they should really. Texas A&M very solid team but a victim of an unfortunate schedule. Easily should match win total or better next year. Mississippi schools with their new coaches will be intriguing.

Tennessee was such a weird team this year. Who knows who shows up in Norman next year... probably a year away from posing a threat in the East, but Pruitt deserves a nod for not letting season derail after losing two home games to non-conference underdogs as well as getting whooped by rivals... they showed resilience and I think they might’ve found their post-Fulmer guy, finally. They’re due a renaissance at some point. Everything is cyclical.

I like Texas A&M as my most improved team in win totals. I like LSU as largest loss in win totals Year over Year (they’ll still be contenders, just damn impossible to match 15 wins)!

Great funny vid!

snippet.textDisplay: Okay I am enjoying National Championship until Spring Football at that point it’s time for me as fan to move on. Now, I’m a realist LSU will have at least eight wins and at most 11 wins. I think Auburn, Bama, Florida, or Georgia can bring home national championship if things fall into place. Also, I will be shocked if Tennessee and Kentucky don’t have betters seasons . I love Muschamp but South Carolina is the wild card. My fellow SEC fans next year will be another fantastic year for our conference. It’s time for the fans and our teams to have much need rest. Good luck on final signing day and we may we all have healthy teams in the spring. Until then! SEC!!!
